$TSLA a little profit taking day does a market good. I take a lot of Vegas trips because it gives indicators and affirmations. 

Here are some assessments made:

1) Middle-class families that got huge wage jumps are still fine. Inflation sucks for them, and they probably cut back some things, but for most part , they are happy, spending, gambling, and fine dining. 

2) Tesla is a top car company period. Their brand is here to stay. Will they continue growth in rate hike hell thats another discussion. 

3) Inflation is still bad and killing lower income families, and rate hikes will continue. Powell strategy has been the same since day 1. Kill growth to kill inflation. Last time I checked, the same a-hole Feds in charge.

4) Market dives rarely come when all expect....very very rare. So either markets will chop till it comes, or they will generate another euphoria bull run before crashing it when it does.

5) Do not believe anyone saying recession won't come. Just dont expect it now.

$TSLA according to Vegas, we still got a while before a real recession. You can't deny there is a lot of Teslas, but I also saw the line for the supercharger station and pretty much laughed at the idea of waiting at one of those. 

The economy is still strong, and yes means more rate hikes, but also means more time. Maybe they can use AI to get momentum for one final run. 

GLTA 🍻

$INTC What got me to early retirement was not marrying a narrative. 

When I entered Intel, I felt that they were grossly undervalued with a secure dividend. The close friends of mine who are managers at their various sites advised me of the positive enertia to change was being felt. 

I cleared my original buys at 28 when hit 30. Now I also sold all my buys at 25 and 26. My same manager friends now speak of how much truly needs to change and how difficult it is to attract real talent. That they did a 5% salary cut across all of Intel. 

The cash erosion is bigger than I expected. Intel will turn around in the end. This is not a LUMN or such. The change is going to take a while. Their cash flows shrinking too fast, and we are not even in the recession yet, which when making 8B in cost saving cuts...to me puts the dividend more at risk than I like at 25/26. Instead, I am going to wait to reposition.

This be a tough yr for Intel. Ill add if goes lower or after if they cut the dividend.

$TSLA The problem is not Tesla....the problem is the Feds. Very few ppl, even upper middle class, just buy their cars outright. The higher these rates go the less people will buy big ticket items. The discounts are great short term. It opens another layer of customers who can instantly jump in. Its not a sustainable model though as rates continue to rise as well as cost of materials. those same ppl will not be able to justify the rate they are offered. Its not being a hater of Tesla that I post more frequently bearish. Its the hater of Powell that does. 

They printed a bunch of money. A lot more ppl are better off with better salaries. Now they want to bleed and take it back. Because in the end its about the people on top. Just never lose sight of that when trying to navigate investing.
